      • insertEdge

        public Edge<U,​V> insertEdge​(int src,
                                  int target,
                                  V data)
        Connects two nodes via an Edge. If an Edge connecting the Nodes already exists, nothing happens, but the Edge will be returned.
        Parameters:
        src - The index of the source node to be connected to the target node.
        target - The index of the target node to be connected to the source node.
        data - The data of the Edge to be created.
        Returns:
        The Edge connecting the Nodes or null if one of the given indices is not associated with a Node.

        public boolean isConnected​(int src,

        Checks whether two Nodes are connected by an Edge.
        Parameters:
        src - The index of the first Node to be checked for a connection.
        target - The index of the second Node to be checked for a connection.
        Returns:
